argumentText:
ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | #P_eflog | |- ( ( A e. CC /\ A =/= 0 ) -> ( exp ` ( log ` A ) ) = A ) |
| 2 | 1 | #P_3adant3 | |- ( ( A e. CC /\ A =/= 0 /\ A =/= 1 ) -> ( exp ` ( log ` A ) ) = A ) |
| 3 |  | #P_simp3 | |- ( ( A e. CC /\ A =/= 0 /\ A =/= 1 ) -> A =/= 1 ) |
| 4 | 2, 3 | #P_eqnetrd | |- ( ( A e. CC /\ A =/= 0 /\ A =/= 1 ) -> ( exp ` ( log ` A ) ) =/= 1 ) |
| 5 | 4 | #P_neneqd | |- ( ( A e. CC /\ A =/= 0 /\ A =/= 1 ) -> -. ( exp ` ( log ` A ) ) = 1 ) |
| 6 |  | #P_fveq2 | |- ( ( log ` A ) = 0 -> ( exp ` ( log ` A ) ) = ( exp ` 0 ) ) |
| 7 |  | #P_ef0 | |- ( exp ` 0 ) = 1 |
| 8 | 6, 7 | #P_syl6eq | |- ( ( log ` A ) = 0 -> ( exp ` ( log ` A ) ) = 1 ) |
| 9 | 8 | #P_necon3bi | |- ( -. ( exp ` ( log ` A ) ) = 1 -> ( log ` A ) =/= 0 ) |
| 10 | 5, 9 | #P_syl | |- ( ( A e. CC /\ A =/= 0 /\ A =/= 1 ) -> ( log ` A ) =/= 0 ) |
\
 log isn't 0 if argument isn't 0 or 1.  Unlike ~ logne0 , this handles complex numbers.  (Contributed by David A. Wheeler, 17-Jul-2017.) (Proof modification is discouraged.)  (New usage is discouraged.)
